{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"For me, this story begins about 15 years ago,"},{"time":4000,"text":"when I was a hospice doctor at the University of Chicago."},{"time":7000,"text":"And I was taking care of people who were dying and their families"},{"time":10000,"text":"in the South Side of Chicago."},{"time":12000,"text":"And I was observing what happened to people and their families"},{"time":15000,"text":"over the course of their terminal illness."},{"time":18000,"text":"And in my lab, I was studying the widower effect,"},{"time":20000,"text":"which is a very old idea in the social sciences,"},{"time":22000,"text":"going back 150 years,"},{"time":24000,"text":"known as \"dying of a broken heart.\""},{"time":26000,"text":"So, when I die, my wife's risk of death can double,"},{"time":29000,"text":"for instance, in the first year."},{"time":31000,"text":"And I had gone to take care of one particular patient,"},{"time":34000,"text":"a woman who was dying of dementia."},{"time":36000,"text":"And in this case, unlike this couple,"},{"time":38000,"text":"she was being cared for"},{"time":40000,"text":"by her daughter."},{"time":42000,"text":"And the daughter was exhausted from caring for her mother."},{"time":45000,"text":"And the daughter's husband,"},{"time":47000,"text":"he also was sick"},{"time":50000,"text":"from his wife's exhaustion."},{"time":52000,"text":"And I was driving home one day,"},{"time":54000,"text":"and I get a phone call from the husband's friend,"},{"time":57000,"text":"calling me because he was depressed"},{"time":59000,"text":"about what was happening to his friend."},{"time":61000,"text":"So here I get this call from this random guy"},{"time":63000,"text":"that's having an experience"},{"time":65000,"text":"that's being influenced by people"},{"time":67000,"text":"at some social distance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69000,"text":"And so I suddenly realized two very simple things:"},{"time":72000,"text":"First, the widowhood effect"},{"time":74000,"text":"was not restricted to husbands and wives."},{"time":77000,"text":"And second, it was not restricted to pairs of people."},{"time":80000,"text":"And I started to see the world"},{"time":82000,"text":"in a whole new way,"},{"time":84000,"text":"like pairs of people connected to each other."},{"time":87000,"text":"And then I realized that these individuals"},{"time":89000,"text":"would be connected into foursomes with other pairs of people nearby."},{"time":92000,"text":"And then, in fact, these people"},{"time":94000,"text":"were embedded in other sorts of relationships:"},{"time":96000,"text":"marriage and spousal"},{"time":98000,"text":"and friendship and other sorts of ties."},{"time":100000,"text":"And that, in fact, these connections were vast"},{"time":103000,"text":"and that we were all embedded in this"},{"time":105000,"text":"broad set of connections with each other."},{"time":108000,"text":"So I started to see the world in a completely new way"},{"time":111000,"text":"and I became obsessed with this."},{"time":113000,"text":"I became obsessed with how it might be"},{"time":115000,"text":"that we're embedded in these social networks,"},{"time":117000,"text":"and how they affect our lives."},{"time":119000,"text":"So, social networks are these intricate things of beauty,"},{"time":122000,"text":"and they're so elaborate and so complex"},{"time":124000,"text":"and so ubiquitous, in fact,"},{"time":126000,"text":"that one has to ask what purpose they serve."},{"time":129000,"text":"Why are we embedded in social networks?"},{"time":131000,"text":"I mean, how do they form? How do they operate?"},{"time":133000,"text":"And how do they effect us?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":135000,"text":"So my first topic with respect to this,"},{"time":138000,"text":"was not death, but obesity."},{"time":141000,"text":"It had become trendy"},{"time":143000,"text":"to speak about the \"obesity epidemic.\""},{"time":145000,"text":"And, along with my collaborator, James Fowler,"},{"time":148000,"text":"we began to wonder whether obesity really was epidemic"},{"time":151000,"text":"and could it spread from person to person"},{"time":153000,"text":"like the four people I discussed earlier."},{"time":156000,"text":"So this is a slide of some of our initial results."},{"time":159000,"text":"It's 2,200 people in the year 2000."},{"time":162000,"text":"Every dot is a person. We make the dot size"},{"time":164000,"text":"proportional to people's body size;"},{"time":166000,"text":"so bigger dots are bigger people."},{"time":169000,"text":"In addition, if your body size,"},{"time":171000,"text":"if your BMI, your body mass index, is above 30 --"},{"time":173000,"text":"if you're clinically obese --"},{"time":175000,"text":"we also colored the dots yellow."},{"time":177000,"text":"So, if you look at this image, right away you might be able to see"},{"time":179000,"text":"that there are clusters of obese and"},{"time":181000,"text":"non-obese people in the image."},{"time":183000,"text":"But the visual complexity is still very high."},{"time":186000,"text":"It's not obvious exactly what's going on."},{"time":189000,"text":"In addition, some questions are immediately raised:"},{"time":191000,"text":"How much clustering is there?"},{"time":193000,"text":"Is there more clustering than would be due to chance alone?"},{"time":196000,"text":"How big are the clusters? How far do they reach?"},{"time":198000,"text":"And, most importantly,"},{"time":200000,"text":"what causes the clusters?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":202000,"text":"So we did some mathematics to study the size of these clusters."},{"time":205000,"text":"This here shows, on the Y-axis,"},{"time":207000,"text":"the increase in the probability that a person is obese"},{"time":210000,"text":"given that a social contact of theirs is obese"},{"time":212000,"text":"and, on the X-axis, the degrees of separation between the two people."},{"time":215000,"text":"On the far left, you see the purple line."},{"time":217000,"text":"It says that, if your friends are obese,"},{"time":219000,"text":"your risk of obesity is 45 percent higher."},{"time":222000,"text":"And the next bar over, the [red] line,"},{"time":224000,"text":"says if your friend's friends are obese,"},{"time":226000,"text":"your risk of obesity is 25 percent higher."},{"time":228000,"text":"And then the next line over says"},{"time":230000,"text":"if your friend's friend's friend, someone you probably don't even know, is obese,"},{"time":233000,"text":"your risk of obesity is 10 percent higher."},{"time":236000,"text":"And it's only when you get to your friend's friend's friend's friends"},{"time":239000,"text":"that there's no longer a relationship"},{"time":241000,"text":"between that person's body size and your own body size."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245000,"text":"Well, what might be causing this clustering?"},{"time":248000,"text":"There are at least three possibilities:"},{"time":250000,"text":"One possibility is that, as I gain weight,"},{"time":252000,"text":"it causes you to gain weight."},{"time":254000,"text":"A kind of induction, a kind of spread from person to person."},{"time":257000,"text":"Another possibility, very obvious, is homophily,"},{"time":259000,"text":"or, birds of a feather flock together;"},{"time":261000,"text":"here, I form my tie to you"},{"time":263000,"text":"because you and I share a similar body size."},{"time":266000,"text":"And the last possibility is what is known as confounding,"},{"time":268000,"text":"because it confounds our ability to figure out what's going on."},{"time":271000,"text":"And here, the idea is not that my weight gain"},{"time":273000,"text":"is causing your weight gain,"},{"time":275000,"text":"nor that I preferentially form a tie with you"},{"time":277000,"text":"because you and I share the same body size,"},{"time":279000,"text":"but rather that we share a common exposure"},{"time":281000,"text":"to something, like a health club"},{"time":284000,"text":"that makes us both lose weight at the same time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287000,"text":"When we studied these data, we found evidence for all of these things,"},{"time":290000,"text":"including for induction."},{"time":292000,"text":"And we found that if your friend becomes obese,"},{"time":294000,"text":"it increases your risk of obesity by about 57 percent"},{"time":297000,"text":"in the same given time period."},{"time":299000,"text":"There can be many mechanisms for this effect:"},{"time":302000,"text":"One possibility is that your friends say to you something like --"},{"time":304000,"text":"you know, they adopt a behavior that spreads to you --"},{"time":307000,"text":"like, they say, \"Let's go have muffins and beer,\""},{"time":310000,"text":"which is a terrible combination. (Laughter)"},{"time":313000,"text":"But you adopt that combination,"},{"time":315000,"text":"and then you start gaining weight like them."},{"time":318000,"text":"Another more subtle possibility"},{"time":320000,"text":"is that they start gaining weight, and it changes your ideas"},{"time":323000,"text":"of what an acceptable body size is."},{"time":325000,"text":"Here, what's spreading from person to person"},{"time":327000,"text":"is not a behavior, but rather a norm:"},{"time":329000,"text":"An idea is spreading."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331000,"text":"Now, headline writers"},{"time":333000,"text":"had a field day with our studies."},{"time":335000,"text":"I think the headline in The New York Times was,"},{"time":337000,"text":"\"Are you packing it on?"},{"time":339000,"text":"Blame your fat friends.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":342000,"text":"What was interesting to us is that the European headline writers"},{"time":344000,"text":"had a different take: They said,"},{"time":346000,"text":"\"Are your friends gaining weight? Perhaps you are to blame.\""},{"time":349000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":354000,"text":"And we thought this was a very interesting comment on America,"},{"time":357000,"text":"and a kind of self-serving,"},{"time":359000,"text":"\"not my responsibility\" kind of phenomenon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361000,"text":"Now, I want to be very clear: We do not think our work"},{"time":363000,"text":"should or could justify prejudice"},{"time":365000,"text":"against people of one or another body size at all."},{"time":369000,"text":"Our next questions was:"},{"time":371000,"text":"Could we actually visualize this spread?"},{"time":374000,"text":"Was weight gain in one person actually spreading"},{"time":376000,"text":"to weight gain in another person?"},{"time":378000,"text":"And this was complicated because"},{"time":380000,"text":"we needed to take into account the fact that the network structure,"},{"time":383000,"text":"the architecture of the ties, was changing across time."},{"time":386000,"text":"In addition, because obesity is not a unicentric epidemic,"},{"time":389000,"text":"there's not a Patient Zero of the obesity epidemic --"},{"time":392000,"text":"if we find that guy, there was a spread of obesity out from him --"},{"time":395000,"text":"it's a multicentric epidemic."},{"time":397000,"text":"Lots of people are doing things at the same time."},{"time":399000,"text":"And I'm about to show you a 30 second video animation"},{"time":402000,"text":"that took me and James five years of our lives to do."},{"time":405000,"text":"So, again, every dot is a person."},{"time":407000,"text":"Every tie between them is a relationship."},{"time":409000,"text":"We're going to put this into motion now,"},{"time":411000,"text":"taking daily cuts through the network for about 30 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414000,"text":"The dot sizes are going to grow,"},{"time":416000,"text":"you're going to see a sea of yellow take over."},{"time":419000,"text":"You're going to see people be born and die --"},{"time":421000,"text":"dots will appear and disappear --"},{"time":423000,"text":"ties will form and break, marriages and divorces,"},{"time":426000,"text":"friendings and defriendings."},{"time":428000,"text":"A lot of complexity, a lot is happening"},{"time":430000,"text":"just in this 30-year period"},{"time":432000,"text":"that includes the obesity epidemic."},{"time":434000,"text":"And, by the end, you're going to see clusters"},{"time":436000,"text":"of obese and non-obese individuals"},{"time":438000,"text":"within the network."},{"time":440000,"text":"Now, when looked at this,"},{"time":443000,"text":"it changed the way I see things,"},{"time":446000,"text":"because this thing, this network"},{"time":448000,"text":"that's changing across time,"},{"time":450000,"text":"it has a memory, it moves,"},{"time":453000,"text":"things flow within it,"},{"time":455000,"text":"it has a kind of consistency --"},{"time":457000,"text":"people can die, but it doesn't die;"},{"time":459000,"text":"it still persists --"},{"time":461000,"text":"and it has a kind of resilience"},{"time":463000,"text":"that allows it to persist across time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465000,"text":"And so, I came to see these kinds of social networks"},{"time":468000,"text":"as living things,"},{"time":470000,"text":"as living things that we could put under a kind of microscope"},{"time":473000,"text":"to study and analyze and understand."},{"time":476000,"text":"And we used a variety of techniques to do this."},{"time":478000,"text":"And we started exploring all kinds of other phenomena."},{"time":481000,"text":"We looked at smoking and drinking behavior,"},{"time":483000,"text":"and voting behavior,"},{"time":485000,"text":"and divorce -- which can spread --"},{"time":487000,"text":"and altruism."},{"time":489000,"text":"And, eventually, we became interested in emotions."},{"time":493000,"text":"Now, when we have emotions,"},{"time":495000,"text":"we show them."},{"time":497000,"text":"Why do we show our emotions?"},{"time":499000,"text":"I mean, there would be an advantage to experiencing"},{"time":501000,"text":"our emotions inside, you know, anger or happiness."},{"time":504000,"text":"But we don't just experience them, we show them."},{"time":506000,"text":"And not only do we show them, but others can read them."},{"time":509000,"text":"And, not only can they read them, but they copy them."},{"time":511000,"text":"There's emotional contagion"},{"time":513000,"text":"that takes place in human populations."},{"time":516000,"text":"And so this function of emotions"},{"time":518000,"text":"suggests that, in addition to any other purpose they serve,"},{"time":520000,"text":"they're a kind of primitive form of communication."},{"time":523000,"text":"And that, in fact, if we really want to understand human emotions,"},{"time":526000,"text":"we need to think about them in this way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528000,"text":"Now, we're accustomed to thinking about emotions in this way,"},{"time":531000,"text":"in simple, sort of, brief periods of time."},{"time":534000,"text":"So, for example,"},{"time":536000,"text":"I was giving this talk recently in New York City,"},{"time":538000,"text":"and I said, \"You know when you're on the subway"},{"time":540000,"text":"and the other person across the subway car"},{"time":542000,"text":"smiles at you,"},{"time":544000,"text":"and you just instinctively smile back?\""},{"time":546000,"text":"And they looked at me and said, \"We don't do that in New York City.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":549000,"text":"And I said, \"Everywhere else in the world,"},{"time":551000,"text":"that's normal human behavior.\""},{"time":553000,"text":"And so there's a very instinctive way"},{"time":555000,"text":"in which we briefly transmit emotions to each other."},{"time":558000,"text":"And, in fact, emotional contagion can be broader still."},{"time":561000,"text":"Like we could have punctuated expressions of anger,"},{"time":564000,"text":"as in riots."},{"time":566000,"text":"The question that we wanted to ask was:"},{"time":568000,"text":"Could emotion spread,"},{"time":570000,"text":"in a more sustained way than riots, across time"},{"time":573000,"text":"and involve large numbers of people,"},{"time":575000,"text":"not just this pair of individuals smiling at each other in the subway car?"},{"time":578000,"text":"Maybe there's a kind of below the surface, quiet riot"},{"time":581000,"text":"that animates us all the time."},{"time":583000,"text":"Maybe there are emotional stampedes"},{"time":585000,"text":"that ripple through social networks."},{"time":587000,"text":"Maybe, in fact, emotions have a collective existence,"},{"time":590000,"text":"not just an individual existence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592000,"text":"And this is one of the first images we made to study this phenomenon."},{"time":595000,"text":"Again, a social network,"},{"time":597000,"text":"but now we color the people yellow if they're happy"},{"time":600000,"text":"and blue if they're sad and green in between."},{"time":603000,"text":"And if you look at this image, you can right away see"},{"time":605000,"text":"clusters of happy and unhappy people,"},{"time":607000,"text":"again, spreading to three degrees of separation."},{"time":609000,"text":"And you might form the intuition"},{"time":611000,"text":"that the unhappy people"},{"time":613000,"text":"occupy a different structural location within the network."},{"time":616000,"text":"There's a middle and an edge to this network,"},{"time":618000,"text":"and the unhappy people seem to be"},{"time":620000,"text":"located at the edges."},{"time":622000,"text":"So to invoke another metaphor,"},{"time":624000,"text":"if you imagine social networks as a kind of"},{"time":626000,"text":"vast fabric of humanity --"},{"time":628000,"text":"I'm connected to you and you to her, on out endlessly into the distance --"},{"time":631000,"text":"this fabric is actually like"},{"time":633000,"text":"an old-fashioned American quilt,"},{"time":635000,"text":"and it has patches on it: happy and unhappy patches."},{"time":638000,"text":"And whether you become happy or not"},{"time":640000,"text":"depends in part on whether you occupy a happy patch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":643000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":645000,"text":"So, this work with emotions,"},{"time":648000,"text":"which are so fundamental,"},{"time":650000,"text":"then got us to thinking about: Maybe"},{"time":652000,"text":"the fundamental causes of human social networks"},{"time":654000,"text":"are somehow encoded in our genes."},{"time":656000,"text":"Because human social networks, whenever they are mapped,"},{"time":659000,"text":"always kind of look like this:"},{"time":661000,"text":"the picture of the network."},{"time":663000,"text":"But they never look like this."},{"time":665000,"text":"Why do they not look like this?"},{"time":667000,"text":"Why don't we form human social networks"},{"time":669000,"text":"that look like a regular lattice?"},{"time":671000,"text":"Well, the striking patterns of human social networks,"},{"time":674000,"text":"their ubiquity and their apparent purpose"},{"time":677000,"text":"beg questions about whether we evolved to have"},{"time":679000,"text":"human social networks in the first place,"},{"time":681000,"text":"and whether we evolved to form networks"},{"time":683000,"text":"with a particular structure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685000,"text":"And notice first of all -- so, to understand this, though,"},{"time":687000,"text":"we need to dissect network structure a little bit first --"},{"time":690000,"text":"and notice that every person in this network"},{"time":692000,"text":"has exactly the same structural location as every other person."},{"time":695000,"text":"But that's not the case with real networks."},{"time":698000,"text":"So, for example, here is a real network of college students"},{"time":700000,"text":"at an elite northeastern university."},{"time":703000,"text":"And now I'm highlighting a few dots."},{"time":705000,"text":"If you look here at the dots,"},{"time":707000,"text":"compare node B in the upper left"},{"time":709000,"text":"to node D in the far right;"},{"time":711000,"text":"B has four friends coming out from him"},{"time":713000,"text":"and D has six friends coming out from him."},{"time":716000,"text":"And so, those two individuals have different numbers of friends."},{"time":719000,"text":"That's very obvious, we all know that."},{"time":721000,"text":"But certain other aspects"},{"time":723000,"text":"of social network structure are not so obvious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725000,"text":"Compare node B in the upper left to node A in the lower left."},{"time":728000,"text":"Now, those people both have four friends,"},{"time":731000,"text":"but A's friends all know each other,"},{"time":733000,"text":"and B's friends do not."},{"time":735000,"text":"So the friend of a friend of A's"},{"time":737000,"text":"is, back again, a friend of A's,"},{"time":739000,"text":"whereas the friend of a friend of B's is not a friend of B's,"},{"time":741000,"text":"but is farther away in the network."},{"time":743000,"text":"This is known as transitivity in networks."},{"time":746000,"text":"And, finally, compare nodes C and D:"},{"time":748000,"text":"C and D both have six friends."},{"time":751000,"text":"If you talk to them, and you said, \"What is your social life like?\""},{"time":754000,"text":"they would say, \"I've got six friends."},{"time":756000,"text":"That's my social experience.\""},{"time":758000,"text":"But now we, with a bird's eye view looking at this network,"},{"time":761000,"text":"can see that they occupy very different social worlds."},{"time":764000,"text":"And I can cultivate that intuition in you by just asking you:"},{"time":766000,"text":"Who would you rather be"},{"time":768000,"text":"if a deadly germ was spreading through the network?"},{"time":770000,"text":"Would you rather be C or D?"},{"time":773000,"text":"You'd rather be D, on the edge of the network."},{"time":775000,"text":"And now who would you rather be"},{"time":777000,"text":"if a juicy piece of gossip -- not about you --"},{"time":780000,"text":"was spreading through the network? (Laughter)"},{"time":782000,"text":"Now, you would rather be C."}]},{"cues":[{"time":784000,"text":"So different structural locations"},{"time":786000,"text":"have different implications for your life."},{"time":788000,"text":"And, in fact, when we did some experiments looking at this,"},{"time":791000,"text":"what we found is that 46 percent of the variation"},{"time":794000,"text":"in how many friends you have"},{"time":796000,"text":"is explained by your genes."},{"time":798000,"text":"And this is not surprising. We know that some people are born shy"},{"time":801000,"text":"and some are born gregarious. That's obvious."},{"time":804000,"text":"But we also found some non-obvious things."},{"time":806000,"text":"For instance, 47 percent in the variation"},{"time":809000,"text":"in whether your friends know each other"},{"time":811000,"text":"is attributable to your genes."},{"time":813000,"text":"Whether your friends know each other"},{"time":815000,"text":"has not just to do with their genes, but with yours."},{"time":818000,"text":"And we think the reason for this is that some people"},{"time":820000,"text":"like to introduce their friends to each other -- you know who you are --"},{"time":823000,"text":"and others of you keep them apart and don't introduce your friends to each other."},{"time":826000,"text":"And so some people knit together the networks around them,"},{"time":829000,"text":"creating a kind of dense web of ties"},{"time":831000,"text":"in which they're comfortably embedded."},{"time":833000,"text":"And finally, we even found that"},{"time":835000,"text":"30 percent of the variation"},{"time":837000,"text":"in whether or not people are in the middle or on the edge of the network"},{"time":840000,"text":"can also be attributed to their genes."},{"time":842000,"text":"So whether you find yourself in the middle or on the edge"},{"time":844000,"text":"is also partially heritable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":847000,"text":"Now, what is the point of this?"},{"time":850000,"text":"How does this help us understand?"},{"time":852000,"text":"How does this help us"},{"time":854000,"text":"figure out some of the problems that are affecting us these days?"},{"time":858000,"text":"Well, the argument I'd like to make is that networks have value."},{"time":861000,"text":"They are a kind of social capital."},{"time":864000,"text":"New properties emerge"},{"time":866000,"text":"because of our embeddedness in social networks,"},{"time":868000,"text":"and these properties inhere"},{"time":871000,"text":"in the structure of the networks,"},{"time":873000,"text":"not just in the individuals within them."},{"time":875000,"text":"So think about these two common objects."},{"time":877000,"text":"They're both made of carbon,"},{"time":879000,"text":"and yet one of them has carbon atoms in it"},{"time":882000,"text":"that are arranged in one particular way -- on the left --"},{"time":885000,"text":"and you get graphite, which is soft and dark."},{"time":888000,"text":"But if you take the same carbon atoms"},{"time":890000,"text":"and interconnect them a different way,"},{"time":892000,"text":"you get diamond, which is clear and hard."},{"time":895000,"text":"And those properties of softness and hardness and darkness and clearness"},{"time":898000,"text":"do not reside in the carbon atoms;"},{"time":900000,"text":"they reside in the interconnections between the carbon atoms,"},{"time":903000,"text":"or at least arise because of the"},{"time":905000,"text":"interconnections between the carbon atoms."},{"time":907000,"text":"So, similarly, the pattern of connections among people"},{"time":910000,"text":"confers upon the groups of people"},{"time":913000,"text":"different properties."},{"time":915000,"text":"It is the ties between people"},{"time":917000,"text":"that makes the whole greater than the sum of its parts."},{"time":920000,"text":"And so it is not just what's happening to these people --"},{"time":923000,"text":"whether they're losing weight or gaining weight, or becoming rich or becoming poor,"},{"time":926000,"text":"or becoming happy or not becoming happy -- that affects us;"},{"time":929000,"text":"it's also the actual architecture"},{"time":931000,"text":"of the ties around us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":933000,"text":"Our experience of the world"},{"time":935000,"text":"depends on the actual structure"},{"time":937000,"text":"of the networks in which we're residing"},{"time":939000,"text":"and on all the kinds of things that ripple and flow"},{"time":942000,"text":"through the network."},{"time":945000,"text":"Now, the reason, I think, that this is the case"},{"time":948000,"text":"is that human beings assemble themselves"},{"time":950000,"text":"and form a kind of superorganism."},{"time":954000,"text":"Now, a superorganism is a collection of individuals"},{"time":957000,"text":"which show or evince behaviors or phenomena"},{"time":960000,"text":"that are not reducible to the study of individuals"},{"time":963000,"text":"and that must be understood by reference to,"},{"time":965000,"text":"and by studying, the collective."},{"time":967000,"text":"Like, for example, a hive of bees"},{"time":970000,"text":"that's finding a new nesting site,"},{"time":973000,"text":"or a flock of birds that's evading a predator,"},{"time":975000,"text":"or a flock of birds that's able to pool its wisdom"},{"time":978000,"text":"and navigate and find a tiny speck"},{"time":980000,"text":"of an island in the middle of the Pacific,"},{"time":982000,"text":"or a pack of wolves that's able"},{"time":984000,"text":"to bring down larger prey."},{"time":987000,"text":"Superorganisms have properties"},{"time":989000,"text":"that cannot be understood just by studying the individuals."},{"time":992000,"text":"I think understanding social networks"},{"time":994000,"text":"and how they form and operate"},{"time":996000,"text":"can help us understand not just health and emotions"},{"time":999000,"text":"but all kinds of other phenomena --"},{"time":1001000,"text":"like crime, and warfare,"},{"time":1003000,"text":"and economic phenomena like bank runs"},{"time":1005000,"text":"and market crashes"},{"time":1007000,"text":"and the adoption of innovation"},{"time":1009000,"text":"and the spread of product adoption."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1011000,"text":"Now, look at this."},{"time":1014000,"text":"I think we form social networks"},{"time":1016000,"text":"because the benefits of a connected life"},{"time":1018000,"text":"outweigh the costs."},{"time":1021000,"text":"If I was always violent towards you"},{"time":1023000,"text":"or gave you misinformation"},{"time":1025000,"text":"or made you sad or infected you with deadly germs,"},{"time":1028000,"text":"you would cut the ties to me,"},{"time":1030000,"text":"and the network would disintegrate."},{"time":1032000,"text":"So the spread of good and valuable things"},{"time":1035000,"text":"is required to sustain and nourish social networks."},{"time":1039000,"text":"Similarly, social networks are required"},{"time":1041000,"text":"for the spread of good and valuable things,"},{"time":1044000,"text":"like love and kindness"},{"time":1046000,"text":"and happiness and altruism"},{"time":1048000,"text":"and ideas."},{"time":1050000,"text":"I think, in fact, that if we realized"},{"time":1052000,"text":"how valuable social networks are,"},{"time":1054000,"text":"we'd spend a lot more time nourishing them and sustaining them,"},{"time":1057000,"text":"because I think social networks"},{"time":1059000,"text":"are fundamentally related to goodness."},{"time":1062000,"text":"And what I think the world needs now"},{"time":1064000,"text":"is more connections."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1066000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1068000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}